-- Sarkozy Narrows Hollande’s Lead to 6 Points in French Election, Poll Shows
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 2012-02-19T09:36:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-19/sarkozy-narrows-hollande-s-lead-to-6-points-in-french-election-poll-shows.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy 
narrowed Socialist rival Francois Hollande’s lead in the run up
to April elections, a poll showed.  Backing for Sarkozy gained 0.5 points to 26 percent since
Feb. 5, while support for Hollande slipped 2 points to 32
percent, according to an LH2 poll for Yahoo! published today.
Support for anti-euro candidate Marine Le Pen dropped 1 point to
14 percent.  LH2 surveyed 967 voters by telephone Feb. 17-18. The poll’s
margin of error is between 2.5 points and 4 points. The first
round of elections is on April 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
